FBIS4-40766 "drsov119__a94014" FBIS-SOV-94-119-A Daily Report 21 June 1994 ANNEX International Affairs Yeltsin Congratulates Chaklov Flight Committee Yeltsin Congratulates Chaklov Flight Committee LD2006115794 Moscow RIA in English 1021 GMT 20 Jun 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY LD2006115794 Moscow RIA English BFN [Text] Moscow, June 20, RIA -- President Boris Yeltsin of the Russian Federation has congratulated the American Chkalov Trans- Polar Flight Committee on its 20th anniversary [as received]. According to the presidential press service, way back in 1937, millions of Russians and Americans had applauded Valeriy Chkalov, Georgiy Baydukov and Aleksandr Belyakov who flew over the north pole all the way to the USA at the time. Yeltsin hailed the committee's noble activities aimed at strengthening mutual understanding between Russia and America and promoting good relations between our two countries, wishing his members and all residents of Vancouver and Portland success in their work, peace, happiness and prosperity.
